131std::tuple<int, bufferlist > rgw_rest_read_all_input(struct req_state *s,
132 const uint64_t max_len,
133 const bool allow_chunked=true);
134
135template <class T>
136int rgw_rest_get_json_input(CephContext *cct, req_state *s, T& out,
137 uint64_t max_len, bool *empty)
138{
139 if (empty)
140 *empty = false;
141
142 int rv = 0;
143 bufferlist data;
144 std::tie(rv, data) = rgw_rest_read_all_input(s, max_len);
145 if (rv < 0) {
146 return rv;
147 }
148
149 if (!data.length()) {
150 if (empty) {
151 *empty = true;
152 }
153
154 return -EINVAL;
155 }
156
157 JSONParser parser;
158
159 if (!parser.parse(data.c_str(), data.length())) {
160 return -EINVAL;
161 }
162
163 try {
164 decode_json_obj(out, &parser);
165 } catch (JSONDecoder::err& e) {
166 return -EINVAL;
167 }
168
169 return 0;
170}

175class RGWOp : public DoutPrefixProvider {
176protected:
177 struct req_state *s;
178 RGWHandler *dialect_handler;
179 rgw::sal::Store* store;
180 RGWCORSConfiguration bucket_cors;
181 bool cors_exist;
182 RGWQuotaInfo bucket_quota;
183 RGWQuotaInfo user_quota;
184 int op_ret;
185 int do_aws4_auth_completion();
186
187 virtual int init_quota();
188
189 std::tuple<int, bufferlist> read_all_input(struct req_state *s,
190 const uint64_t max_len,
191 const bool allow_chunked=true) {
192
193 int rv = 0;
194 bufferlist data;
195 std::tie(rv, data) = rgw_rest_read_all_input(s, max_len);
196 if (rv >= 0) {
197 do_aws4_auth_completion();
198 }
199
200 return std::make_tuple(rv, std::move(data));
201 }
202
203 template <class T>
204 int get_json_input(CephContext *cct, req_state *s, T& out,
205 uint64_t max_len, bool *empty) {
206 int r = rgw_rest_get_json_input(cct, s, out, max_len, empty);
207 if (r >= 0) {
208 do_aws4_auth_completion();
209 }
210 return r;
211 }
212
213public:
214 RGWOp()
215 : s(nullptr),
216 dialect_handler(nullptr),
217 store(nullptr),
218 cors_exist(false),
219 op_ret(0) {
220 }
221
222 virtual ~RGWOp() override;
223
224 int get_ret() const { return op_ret; }
225
226 virtual int init_processing(optional_yield y) {
227 if (dialect_handler->supports_quota()) {
228 op_ret = init_quota();
229 if (op_ret < 0)
230 return op_ret;
231 }
232
233 return 0;
234 }
235
236 virtual void init(rgw::sal::Store* store, struct req_state *s, RGWHandler *dialect_handler) {
237 this->store = store;
238 this->s = s;
239 this->dialect_handler = dialect_handler;
240 }
241 int read_bucket_cors();
242 bool generate_cors_headers(std::string& origin, std::string& method, std::string& headers, std::string& exp_headers, unsigned *max_age);
243
244 virtual int verify_params() { return 0; }
245 virtual bool prefetch_data() { return false; }
246
247 /* Authenticate requester -- verify its identity.
248 *
249 * NOTE: typically the procedure is common across all operations of the same
250 * dialect (S3, Swift API). However, there are significant exceptions in
251 * both APIs: browser uploads, /info and OPTIONS handlers. All of them use
252 * different, specific authentication schema driving the need for per-op
253 * authentication. The alternative is to duplicate parts of the method-
254 * dispatch logic in RGWHandler::authorize() and pollute it with a lot
255 * of special cases. */
256 virtual int verify_requester(const rgw::auth::StrategyRegistry& auth_registry, optional_yield y) {
257 /* TODO(rzarzynski): rename RGWHandler::authorize to generic_authenticate. */
258 return dialect_handler->authorize(this, y);
259 }
260 virtual int verify_permission(optional_yield y) = 0;
261 virtual int verify_op_mask();
262 virtual void pre_exec() {}
263 virtual void execute(optional_yield y) = 0;
264 virtual void send_response() {}
265 virtual void complete() {
266 send_response();
267 }
268 virtual const char* name() const = 0;
269 virtual RGWOpType get_type() { return RGW_OP_UNKNOWN; }
270
271 virtual uint32_t op_mask() { return 0; }
272
273 virtual int error_handler(int err_no, std::string *error_content, optional_yield y);
274
275 // implements DoutPrefixProvider
276 std::ostream& gen_prefix(std::ostream& out) const override;
277 CephContext* get_cct() const override { return s->cct; }
278 unsigned get_subsys() const override { return ceph_subsys_rgw; }
279
280 virtual dmc::client_id dmclock_client() { return dmc::client_id::metadata; }
281 virtual dmc::Cost dmclock_cost() { return 1; }
282 virtual void write_ops_log_entry(rgw_log_entry& entry) const {};
283};

2109static inline void format_xattr(std::string &xattr)
2110{
2111 /* If the extended attribute is not valid UTF-8, we encode it using
2112 * quoted-printable encoding.
2113 */
2114 if ((check_utf8(xattr.c_str(), xattr.length()) != 0) ||
2115 (check_for_control_characters(xattr.c_str(), xattr.length()) != 0)) {
2116 static const char MIME_PREFIX_STR[] = "=?UTF-8?Q?";
2117 static const int MIME_PREFIX_LEN = sizeof(MIME_PREFIX_STR) - 1;
2118 static const char MIME_SUFFIX_STR[] = "?=";
2119 static const int MIME_SUFFIX_LEN = sizeof(MIME_SUFFIX_STR) - 1;
2120 int mlen = mime_encode_as_qp(xattr.c_str(), NULL, 0);
2121 char *mime = new char[MIME_PREFIX_LEN + mlen + MIME_SUFFIX_LEN + 1];
2122 strcpy(mime, MIME_PREFIX_STR);
2123 mime_encode_as_qp(xattr.c_str(), mime + MIME_PREFIX_LEN, mlen);
2124 strcpy(mime + MIME_PREFIX_LEN + (mlen - 1), MIME_SUFFIX_STR);
2125 xattr.assign(mime);
2126 delete [] mime;
2127 }
2128} /* format_xattr */

2139inline int rgw_get_request_metadata(const DoutPrefixProvider *dpp,
2140 CephContext* const cct,
2141 struct req_info& info,
2142 std::map<std::string, ceph::bufferlist>& attrs,
2143 const bool allow_empty_attrs = true)
2144{
2145 static const std::set<std::string> blocklisted_headers = {
2146 "x-amz-server-side-encryption-customer-algorithm",
2147 "x-amz-server-side-encryption-customer-key",
2148 "x-amz-server-side-encryption-customer-key-md5",
2149 "x-amz-storage-class"
2150 };
2151
2152 size_t valid_meta_count = 0;
2153 for (auto& kv : info.x_meta_map) {
2154 const std::string& name = kv.first;
2155 std::string& xattr = kv.second;
2156
2157 if (blocklisted_headers.count(name) == 1) {
2158 ldpp_subdout(dpp, rgw, 10) << "skipping x>> " << name << dendl;
2159 continue;
2160 } else if (allow_empty_attrs || !xattr.empty()) {
2161 ldpp_subdout(dpp, rgw, 10) << "x>> " << name << ":" << xattr << dendl;
2162 format_xattr(xattr);
2163
2164 std::string attr_name(RGW_ATTR_PREFIX);
2165 attr_name.append(name);
2166
2167 /* Check roughly whether we aren't going behind the limit on attribute
2168 * name. Passing here doesn't guarantee that an OSD will accept that
2169 * as ObjectStore::get_max_attr_name_length() can set the limit even
2170 * lower than the "osd_max_attr_name_len" configurable. */
2171 const auto max_attr_name_len = cct->_conf->rgw_max_attr_name_len;
2172 if (max_attr_name_len && attr_name.length() > max_attr_name_len) {
2173 return -ENAMETOOLONG;
2174 }
2175
2176 /* Similar remarks apply to the check for value size. We're veryfing
2177 * it early at the RGW's side as it's being claimed in /info. */
2178 const auto max_attr_size = cct->_conf->rgw_max_attr_size;
2179 if (max_attr_size && xattr.length() > max_attr_size) {
2180 return -EFBIG;
2181 }
2182
2183 /* Swift allows administrators to limit the number of metadats items
2184 * send _in a single request_. */
2185 const auto max_attrs_num_in_req = cct->_conf->rgw_max_attrs_num_in_req;
2186 if (max_attrs_num_in_req &&
2187 ++valid_meta_count > max_attrs_num_in_req) {
2188 return -E2BIG;
2189 }
2190
2191 auto rval = attrs.emplace(std::move(attr_name), ceph::bufferlist());
2192 /* At the moment the value of the freshly created attribute key-value
2193 * pair is an empty bufferlist. */
2194
2195 ceph::bufferlist& bl = rval.first->second;
2196 bl.append(xattr.c_str(), xattr.size() + 1);
2197 }
2198 }
2199
2200 return 0;
2201} /* rgw_get_request_metadata */

2605inline int parse_value_and_bound(
2606 const std::string &input,
2607 int &output,
2608 const long lower_bound,
2609 const long upper_bound,
2610 const long default_val)
2611{
2612 if (!input.empty()) {
2613 char *endptr;
2614 output = strtol(input.c_str(), &endptr, 10);
2615 if (endptr) {
2616 if (endptr == input.c_str()) return -EINVAL;
2617 while (*endptr && isspace(*endptr)) // ignore white space
2618 endptr++;
2619 if (*endptr) {
2620 return -EINVAL;
2621 }
2622 }
2623 if(output > upper_bound) {
2624 output = upper_bound;
2625 }
2626 if(output < lower_bound) {
2627 output = lower_bound;
2628 }
2629 } else {
2630 output = default_val;
2631 }
2632
2633 return 0;
2634}
